        correct: 1,
        rationale: "Celiac disease causes villous atrophy in the small intestine, reducing levothyroxine absorption. Patients with celiac disease on a gluten-free diet may see improved absorption and require dose reduction. Tirosint (gelcap formulation) may offer better absorption in malabsorption conditions."
