    pearls: ["The degree of RVOT obstruction determines clinical severity: mild obstruction = 'pink' TOF with minimal cyanosis; severe obstruction = severe cyanosis with tet spells","Knee-to-chest positioning during tet spells INCREASES systemic vascular resistance (compresses femoral arteries), which DECREASES right-to-left shunting and INCREASES pulmonary blood flow","A LOUDER murmur in TOF indicates LESS obstruction (more blood flowing through the stenotic RVOT); during a tet spell, the murmur becomes SOFTER or disappears as blood shunts away from the lungs","Boot-shaped heart on chest X-ray (coeur en sabot) is the classic radiographic finding of TOF","22q11.2 deletion (DiGeorge syndrome) is present in 15-25% of TOF patients — all TOF patients should be tested; associated with immune deficiency, hypocalcemia, and palatal abnormalities","Prostaglandin E1: maintain PDA patency in ductal-dependent TOF; most important side effect is APNEA — have intubation equipment at bedside","Post-surgical right bundle branch block (RBBB) is EXPECTED after TOF repair due to surgical disruption of the right ventricular outflow tract; pulmonary regurgitation is the most common long-term sequela"],
